Compilation info
A nine disc retrospective of US American pop music between the years 1897 to 1946.

Truly everything an archivist, audiophile, historian, or folk/blues/country/jazz/pop completist could ever want.

Included are 300DPI scans of the entire 3-booklet, 127 page artist/track commentary.

This collection is currently out of print and is not available for purchase anywhere that I was able to discover. So here it is!

Reviews/info:
http://www.venerablemusic.com/catalog/TitleDetails.asp?TitleID=8794
"An outstanding collection of rare jazz, blues, country, pop, cowboy, march, ragtime, vaudeville and gospel recordings that form our musical legacy, compiled by the well known saxophonist and jazz historian Allen Lowe. The collection consists of nine CD's containing more than 10 hours of music in a presentation slipcase with a 127 page booklet containing many photos and a wealth of interesting information about the music."
